# API Design

- Preserve simplified OpenAI-compatible chat completion request and response shapes.
- Validate incoming requests before provider routing.
- Return clean JSON errors and avoid leaking internal errors to clients.
- Include request IDs in responses and error bodies when available.
- Keep `/health` and `/ready` lightweight.
- Keep examples synchronized with actual request and response structs.
- Core request fields: required `model`, non-empty `messages`, `role`, `content`, optional `temperature`, optional `max_tokens`.
- Valid roles are `system`, `user`, and `assistant`.
- Core response fields: `id`, `object`, `created`, `model`, `provider`, `choices`, and `usage`.
